> ```
>  
> If you look at the code at Inner and at FailAsyncDelegateTask they are the same.
> But when I look at the debug information, I don't see any sequence point generated for the lines of the Inner method, but I see normal sequence points for FailAsyncDelegateTask method.
> The same thing happens with lambdas, the sequence points are not generated when Runtime Async is enabled.
> If I compile the same code with Runtime Async disabled I can correctly see the sequence points for Inner and FailAsyncDelegateTask. 

